In a speech at the South Court Auditorium, President Biden emphasized the urgency of taking action to address climate change. He called for stronger commitments and actions from all nations to limit global warming to 1.5 degrees Celsius. The President highlighted the progress made by the United States in the fight against climate change, including the signing of the Inflation Reduction Act, the largest investment in fighting climate change in history. He also mentioned the ratification of the Kigali Amendment and the reduction of emissions through measures like decarbonizing energy and ending deforestation. President Biden encouraged other countries to join in these efforts and announced that the United States will contribute $1 billion to the Green Climate Fund. He concluded by emphasizing the importance of collective action and collaboration in addressing the climate crisis.